==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|cognicion}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|cognitio||knowledge, perception, a judicial examination, trial}}, from {{term|cognitus}}, past participle of {{term|cognoscere||to know}}, from {{term|co-||together}} + *{{term||gnoscere}}, older form of {{term|noscere||to know}}; see [[know]], and compare [[cognize]], [[cognizance]], [[cognizor]], [[cognosce]], [[connoisseur]].

